WEBVTT

00:00:13.105 --> 00:00:17.145
I agreed to the treatment because
I thought you could make me better.

00:00:17.225 --> 00:00:19.265
But you refused to treat me yourself.

00:00:19.825 --> 00:00:21.785
If you don’t drink with me,
I’m cutting your pay.

00:00:21.865 --> 00:00:22.985
Do whatever you want.

00:00:23.065 --> 00:00:26.505
You two are quite something. The other
day you almost wrecked the kitchen.

00:00:26.585 --> 00:00:28.025
When did you two become so close?

00:00:28.105 --> 00:00:29.585
I'm thinking about quitting the host job.

00:00:29.665 --> 00:00:31.705
I usually eat alone.

00:00:31.785 --> 00:00:34.585
But… having you here
as a friend isn't bad either.

00:00:34.665 --> 00:00:36.745
Even if I can't be your doctor,

00:00:36.825 --> 00:00:37.865
I promise you.

00:00:37.945 --> 00:00:40.305
I will do everything
in my power to help you get better.

00:00:40.385 --> 00:00:42.065
Please, trust me.

00:01:53.905 --> 00:01:55.145
It is ready to eat?

00:01:55.225 --> 00:01:57.585
Here, this piece is perfect.

00:01:58.985 --> 00:02:00.905
-Have one more.
-Thanks.

00:02:00.985 --> 00:02:03.025
-Is that enough?
-I'll come back for more.

00:02:03.105 --> 00:02:04.305
Pi Doc,

00:02:05.665 --> 00:02:09.065
thanks for inviting me to…

00:02:09.144 --> 00:02:10.465
your family party.

00:02:15.105 --> 00:02:16.345
Your family is…

00:02:16.865 --> 00:02:18.265
quite big, isn't it?

00:02:20.185 --> 00:02:21.385
You bet it is.

00:02:21.905 --> 00:02:24.745
Actually, my siblings are
over there. That's Tawan. Tawan!

00:02:25.585 --> 00:02:26.585
Show your hand!

00:02:28.425 --> 00:02:32.305
And that guy posing over there,
not sure if he's drunk yet,

00:02:32.385 --> 00:02:33.185
is Sky.

00:02:35.105 --> 00:02:38.505
And the youngest one is Looksoh.

00:02:44.105 --> 00:02:44.945
But…

00:02:45.465 --> 00:02:47.105
how come you and your siblings…

00:02:47.185 --> 00:02:48.745
don't really look alike?

00:02:49.265 --> 00:02:50.625
I knew you were going to ask.

00:02:51.545 --> 00:02:54.025
Tawan, Sky, and I…

00:02:54.745 --> 00:02:56.505
Mom adopted us when we were little.

00:02:57.545 --> 00:02:59.345
Only Looksoh

00:02:59.905 --> 00:03:01.545
is her own daughter.

00:03:03.065 --> 00:03:05.225
That's so heartwarming.

00:03:05.305 --> 00:03:07.745
Heartwarming?
We've been fighting since we were kids.

00:03:07.825 --> 00:03:08.985
Sky!

00:03:09.585 --> 00:03:10.545
You’re asking for it!

00:03:11.265 --> 00:03:12.425
I'm scared.

00:03:14.105 --> 00:03:15.945
And what about him?

00:03:17.225 --> 00:03:19.745
Is he Pi Sky's boyfriend?

00:03:23.025 --> 00:03:24.345
Oh, this is Nava.

00:03:25.065 --> 00:03:25.985
We're just friends.

00:03:33.945 --> 00:03:35.265
And Mr. Singer,

00:03:35.785 --> 00:03:37.985
are you going to sing here tonight?

00:03:38.065 --> 00:03:39.385
This "Mr. Singer?"

00:03:40.825 --> 00:03:42.345
He's the pastry boy at my café.

00:03:43.265 --> 00:03:44.105
DinDin.

00:03:46.345 --> 00:03:47.825
Hi, Sailom.

00:03:49.225 --> 00:03:50.345
Hey, DinDin.

00:03:50.865 --> 00:03:52.065
Grab some refills from the car.

00:03:53.625 --> 00:03:54.665
Sure thing, old man.

00:03:59.065 --> 00:04:01.425
-Does my shirt smell?
-Let me see.

00:04:03.225 --> 00:04:05.345
-Hmm… smells like heaven.
-Wanna hear me singing?

00:04:05.425 --> 00:04:06.505
Yep.

00:04:06.585 --> 00:04:08.505
Any song you can sing.

00:04:11.385 --> 00:04:12.905
I'm just background noise.

00:04:13.465 --> 00:04:14.905
Gonna be an extra one day.

00:04:42.705 --> 00:04:46.345
I used to have a family like yours.

00:04:49.065 --> 00:04:50.065
Used to?

00:04:50.865 --> 00:04:52.425
What about now?

00:04:53.985 --> 00:04:56.425
I'm on my own now.

00:05:00.305 --> 00:05:01.305
How?

00:05:05.225 --> 00:05:06.185
Well…

00:05:07.305 --> 00:05:08.505
My dad was a funny guy,

00:05:10.585 --> 00:05:12.425
and my mom was the kindest person.

00:05:14.025 --> 00:05:15.265
Dad always said

00:05:15.825 --> 00:05:17.905
he wanted me to live a happy life.

00:05:18.905 --> 00:05:19.745
But…

00:05:20.265 --> 00:05:23.225
how can you be happy without money?

00:05:24.145 --> 00:05:25.025
True.

00:05:27.305 --> 00:05:29.305
And why did they…?

00:05:30.905 --> 00:05:32.265
A car accident.

00:05:41.785 --> 00:05:43.345
I can be your family.

00:05:45.145 --> 00:05:46.065
And…

00:05:46.585 --> 00:05:48.145
what kind of family would you be for me?

00:05:51.185 --> 00:05:52.065
I…

00:05:52.705 --> 00:05:54.225
can be anything.

00:05:55.185 --> 00:05:56.785
Whatever you want me to be.

00:05:58.505 --> 00:06:00.905
A father figure,

00:06:01.745 --> 00:06:02.905
a friend,

00:06:04.345 --> 00:06:05.905
a brother,

00:06:06.425 --> 00:06:07.945
or even just a friend.

00:06:09.905 --> 00:06:10.945
What about a boyfriend?

00:06:16.425 --> 00:06:17.785
I want to know…

00:06:18.625 --> 00:06:20.505
what it feels like to have one.

00:06:25.305 --> 00:06:26.545
You've never had a boyfriend before?

00:06:28.825 --> 00:06:31.745
I just work to make money.

00:06:33.665 --> 00:06:35.185
Never had a single one.

00:06:40.865 --> 00:06:42.025
So…

00:06:45.065 --> 00:06:46.105
give me a kiss.

00:06:48.465 --> 00:06:49.905
The vibe is just right.

00:06:58.065 --> 00:06:59.745
But no "business kiss."

00:07:11.225 --> 00:07:12.465
That kiss was free of charge.

00:07:24.505 --> 00:07:25.905
And this one…

00:07:26.665 --> 00:07:28.145
a kiss between boyfriends.

00:07:53.425 --> 00:07:54.705
Boyfriends kiss?

00:07:55.705 --> 00:07:56.825
Uh-huh.

00:08:29.745 --> 00:08:30.745
What are you doing?

00:08:33.745 --> 00:08:36.185
Planning to take leftovers home every day?

00:08:38.385 --> 00:08:42.425
Geez… don't be so stingy.

00:08:52.665 --> 00:08:53.585
What are you doing?

00:08:56.185 --> 00:08:57.425
Cooking.

00:09:12.225 --> 00:09:13.145
Know how to stir-fry?

00:09:15.225 --> 00:09:16.225
What do you think?

00:09:29.985 --> 00:09:31.185
Here.

00:09:32.745 --> 00:09:35.945
Take this home, so your
grandma can have a warm meal.

00:09:38.145 --> 00:09:40.065
Why are you so unusually nice today?

00:09:41.105 --> 00:09:42.825
You want it or not? I'll just eat--

00:09:42.905 --> 00:09:44.185
I want it!

00:09:44.265 --> 00:09:45.105
Whoa…

00:09:45.745 --> 00:09:46.785
I want it.

00:09:48.345 --> 00:09:49.585
Thanks, old man.

00:09:54.105 --> 00:09:55.465
Grandma, I'm home!

00:09:55.545 --> 00:09:56.745
Oh, you're back?

00:09:56.825 --> 00:09:58.585
Yeah. And I brought some curry too.

00:09:58.665 --> 00:09:59.665
Okay.

00:10:00.425 --> 00:10:01.465
Here.

00:10:02.745 --> 00:10:03.665
Let’s eat.

00:10:04.305 --> 00:10:06.545
Oh dear, I’m already full.

00:10:06.625 --> 00:10:07.945
Let’s save it for tomorrow.

00:10:08.025 --> 00:10:10.745
-Alright?
-Please eat with me.

00:10:11.305 --> 00:10:13.465
-But I just ate.
-Please? Just a little bit?

00:10:13.545 --> 00:10:14.785
Alright.

00:10:14.865 --> 00:10:17.225
-Just a bite or two then.
-A bite or two is perfect.

00:10:17.305 --> 00:10:19.265
Let me help you unwrap these.

00:10:19.345 --> 00:10:23.585
-Just a second, you must be starving.
-Yes, I am.

00:10:23.665 --> 00:10:25.585
Let me get the plates ready.

00:10:26.825 --> 00:10:28.065
Alright!

00:10:34.345 --> 00:10:35.585
Smells okay, I guess.

00:10:36.705 --> 00:10:37.625
Give it back then.

00:10:37.705 --> 00:10:39.665
No way. It smells amazing.

00:10:41.545 --> 00:10:42.545
Thanks again.

00:11:01.545 --> 00:11:02.945
Who do you live here with?

00:11:04.785 --> 00:11:05.945
I live with my dad.

00:11:08.585 --> 00:11:11.465
But he has businesses all over,

00:11:11.545 --> 00:11:12.865
so he's rarely home.

00:11:20.945 --> 00:11:22.625
Actually, he's never home.

00:11:27.665 --> 00:11:31.545
Since I got back from America,

00:11:32.545 --> 00:11:34.585
I've barely seen his face.

00:11:36.025 --> 00:11:37.505
Like last week,

00:11:38.025 --> 00:11:40.025
he was working in Chiang Mai.

00:11:40.985 --> 00:11:42.385
When he got back…

00:11:43.665 --> 00:11:45.825
he had to fly to Singapore for a meeting.

00:11:46.585 --> 00:11:50.265
And now, he’s in
Hat Yai for another project.

00:11:52.345 --> 00:11:56.745
I’m not sure if he works this hard

00:11:58.705 --> 00:12:01.865
because he wants to provide for me

00:12:04.825 --> 00:12:05.825
or…

00:12:07.665 --> 00:12:09.345
if he just doesn’t want to see me.

00:12:11.985 --> 00:12:13.105
Well…

00:12:15.505 --> 00:12:18.065
my parents split up when I was a kid.

00:12:22.225 --> 00:12:24.705
And back then,
I chose to stay with my mom.

00:12:30.345 --> 00:12:32.425
Maybe my dad is still mad at me

00:12:32.985 --> 00:12:34.625
because I didn't choose him.

00:12:38.545 --> 00:12:40.265
So now, he’s getting back at me.

00:12:45.105 --> 00:12:46.345
The truth is…

00:12:46.425 --> 00:12:48.465
I never wanted to choose at all.

00:12:51.425 --> 00:12:53.425
Because no matter who I chose…

00:12:54.665 --> 00:12:56.585
I would still be the one at fault.

00:12:59.905 --> 00:13:01.465
But not choosing…

00:13:03.585 --> 00:13:04.745
wasn't an option.

00:13:12.265 --> 00:13:13.665
I'm sorry for

00:13:13.745 --> 00:13:16.025
rambling on about my problems.

00:13:22.585 --> 00:13:23.785
It’s okay.

00:13:26.025 --> 00:13:29.185
I’m right here,
and I’ll listen to everything you say.

00:13:52.865 --> 00:13:54.745
Grandma! Grandma!

00:13:55.305 --> 00:13:57.865
Grandma! Grandma!

00:13:58.825 --> 00:14:01.065
What’s wrong, Grandma? Grandma!

00:14:02.265 --> 00:14:03.265
Grandma!

00:14:07.505 --> 00:14:08.345
Hello.

00:14:09.145 --> 00:14:10.025
Hello, Tawan!

00:14:10.105 --> 00:14:11.505
Help me! My grandma collapsed!

00:14:14.905 --> 00:14:15.745
Grandma!

00:14:22.865 --> 00:14:23.905
DinDin.

00:14:24.705 --> 00:14:25.945
Don't stress too much.

00:14:32.865 --> 00:14:34.465
What if something happens to her?

00:14:36.305 --> 00:14:37.185
DinDin.

00:14:39.585 --> 00:14:42.145
Your grandma is going to be okay.

00:14:51.105 --> 00:14:52.105
You can hold it.

00:14:56.985 --> 00:14:57.945
My hand is free.

00:15:38.145 --> 00:15:40.625
Welcome to Love Like a Bike.

00:15:52.105 --> 00:15:53.025
Phailin.

00:16:04.585 --> 00:16:05.585
Phailin,

00:16:06.865 --> 00:16:08.385
I want to see Nabnueng.

00:16:41.345 --> 00:16:43.225
Hello? What's up, Papp?

00:16:43.865 --> 00:16:46.745
Sky! What the hell are you doing?

00:16:46.825 --> 00:16:48.625
Are you quitting or staying?

00:16:48.705 --> 00:16:52.465
Come talk to Madam Amy and clear this up.

00:16:53.425 --> 00:16:55.865
Alright, I'm coming in.

00:17:01.945 --> 00:17:03.065
Where are you going?

00:17:03.145 --> 00:17:04.585
To the club.

00:17:04.665 --> 00:17:06.184
I need to clear things up.

00:17:06.265 --> 00:17:07.224
I'll be back soon.

00:17:08.224 --> 00:17:09.464
Clear things up?

00:17:09.545 --> 00:17:11.025
About what?

00:17:13.224 --> 00:17:15.825
About my resignation.

00:17:15.905 --> 00:17:17.305
I want to settle everything.

00:17:19.464 --> 00:17:20.944
Let me know if I can help you.

00:17:29.265 --> 00:17:30.585
Be right back.

00:17:45.425 --> 00:17:47.505
If you've decided to quit,

00:17:47.585 --> 00:17:49.305
I won't hold you back.

00:17:50.865 --> 00:17:53.985
A job like ours requires your whole heart.

00:17:54.665 --> 00:17:58.585
If your heart isn't in it anymore,
there's nothing I can do.

00:17:58.665 --> 00:18:00.225
Good luck with everything, Son.

00:18:01.945 --> 00:18:04.985
Thank you so much, Madam,
for understanding.

00:18:05.065 --> 00:18:09.745
I do. But leaving so suddenly
puts me in a tough spot.

00:18:10.625 --> 00:18:14.065
Man pre-ordered 500 drinks,

00:18:14.145 --> 00:18:16.425
and I've already accepted the payment.

00:18:17.465 --> 00:18:18.785
Since you're here tonight,

00:18:20.025 --> 00:18:23.305
could you work one last shift for me?

00:18:25.105 --> 00:18:27.985
Madam, I just…

00:18:28.585 --> 00:18:29.425
Please.

00:18:36.025 --> 00:18:36.985
I will do it.

00:18:38.345 --> 00:18:39.225
Good luck, Son.

00:18:40.225 --> 00:18:41.305
And thank you.

00:18:46.625 --> 00:18:48.265
I heard you're quitting the host job.

00:18:52.585 --> 00:18:53.545
Yes.

00:18:55.825 --> 00:18:56.945
Is it because of that guy?

00:19:00.545 --> 00:19:01.465
Pi Man,

00:19:03.425 --> 00:19:06.025
I know how you feel about me.

00:19:07.945 --> 00:19:10.385
And I'm truly grateful

00:19:10.465 --> 00:19:12.785
for everything you've done for me.

00:19:14.585 --> 00:19:15.585
But I’ve…

00:19:16.905 --> 00:19:19.305
never felt anything for you beyond…

00:19:19.945 --> 00:19:22.145
a host and a customer.

00:19:24.545 --> 00:19:25.825
What makes him better than me?

00:19:27.145 --> 00:19:28.745
Why choose him?

00:19:31.425 --> 00:19:32.985
He's not better than you,

00:19:33.865 --> 00:19:35.825
and you're not better than him.

00:19:36.905 --> 00:19:38.705
You're just different.

00:19:39.345 --> 00:19:42.745
But you of all people should know

00:19:42.825 --> 00:19:45.585
that love doesn't need a reason.

00:19:53.225 --> 00:19:54.145
Fine!

00:19:54.225 --> 00:19:56.185
If this is your last night…

00:19:58.865 --> 00:20:00.865
can you give me your all?

00:20:03.545 --> 00:20:04.505
I will.

00:20:29.145 --> 00:20:30.905
Are you really quitting?

00:20:31.625 --> 00:20:32.625
Are you sure about this?

00:20:37.025 --> 00:20:38.105
I'm not sure.

00:20:40.785 --> 00:20:42.665
A host and a customer.

00:20:42.745 --> 00:20:43.985
Is it really possible?

00:20:49.025 --> 00:20:52.065
Customers and hosts are human beings.

00:20:52.145 --> 00:20:53.505
We just have to give it a shot.

00:20:55.225 --> 00:20:58.185
Alright. Do whatever makes you happy.

00:20:58.265 --> 00:21:01.465
But if you ever get hurt,
I'm always here to open a bottle for you.

00:21:02.825 --> 00:21:04.265
Thanks.

00:21:23.705 --> 00:21:25.305
Hey, Nava. You still awake?

00:21:30.585 --> 00:21:31.425
I miss you too.

00:21:32.665 --> 00:21:33.905
I'll be there soon.

00:21:41.185 --> 00:21:42.265
I'm heading out.

00:21:43.945 --> 00:21:44.985
Clear this for me.

00:22:05.465 --> 00:22:07.425
TANWARIN HOSPITAL

00:22:11.825 --> 00:22:12.985
Who was that?

00:22:14.225 --> 00:22:15.225
Just an old friend.

00:22:16.265 --> 00:22:17.385
Why didn't you pick up?

00:22:18.185 --> 00:22:19.145
Don't feel like talking.

00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:27.585
A morning kiss.

00:22:35.585 --> 00:22:38.025
I quit the club last night.

00:22:39.065 --> 00:22:40.145
From now on,

00:22:41.185 --> 00:22:44.065
I'm no longer "Sky the host."

00:22:44.145 --> 00:22:45.385
I'm just Sky…

00:22:46.185 --> 00:22:48.745
your boyfriend.

00:22:52.985 --> 00:22:54.145
So…

00:22:54.225 --> 00:22:57.425
what's your plan now that you've quit?

00:22:58.865 --> 00:23:00.345
For now?

00:23:00.865 --> 00:23:02.305
Just resting.

00:23:02.945 --> 00:23:05.145
I want to spend every
moment with you like this.

00:23:07.545 --> 00:23:08.905
So sweet.

00:23:11.305 --> 00:23:12.905
I do have a plan.

00:23:13.425 --> 00:23:16.065
I want to go help with the family cafe.

00:23:16.585 --> 00:23:18.185
Business hasn't been great lately.

00:23:20.545 --> 00:23:21.985
I'm thinking of…

00:23:22.505 --> 00:23:24.825
expanding the bike shop.

00:23:24.905 --> 00:23:27.265
Instead of just repairs,

00:23:27.345 --> 00:23:29.305
I'll turn it into the biggest hub

00:23:29.385 --> 00:23:33.025
for bike parts in the neighborhood.

00:23:33.105 --> 00:23:36.745
The biggest? That shop is tiny.

00:23:36.825 --> 00:23:38.425
It’s just a thought.

00:23:39.425 --> 00:23:41.625
But you never know.

00:23:41.705 --> 00:23:44.025
What about you? Any plans?

00:23:51.705 --> 00:23:52.545
None.

00:23:54.985 --> 00:23:56.065
Oh, wait…

00:23:57.425 --> 00:23:59.025
What did you do before this?

00:23:59.105 --> 00:24:00.665
I mean, what was your job?

00:24:03.425 --> 00:24:05.865
I was in… production.

00:24:07.025 --> 00:24:08.305
Really?

00:24:09.345 --> 00:24:10.865
That's perfect.

00:24:10.945 --> 00:24:14.105
Once I turn the shop into a big hub,

00:24:14.185 --> 00:24:16.665
you can handle the production
and promote the café.

00:24:16.745 --> 00:24:19.505
It'll help get our name out there.

00:24:19.585 --> 00:24:21.025
By the way,

00:24:21.105 --> 00:24:24.225
we could even turn the shop into a studio.

00:24:24.305 --> 00:24:26.665
Why don’t we open it together?

00:24:26.745 --> 00:24:27.825
It'd be awesome.

00:24:35.665 --> 00:24:36.745
Sky…

00:24:40.465 --> 00:24:41.745
give me a kiss.

00:24:44.545 --> 00:24:46.345
Can you kiss me…

00:24:47.545 --> 00:24:49.025
like it's our last day together?

00:24:56.105 --> 00:24:58.385
Where is this coming from?

00:25:01.025 --> 00:25:02.065
Well…

00:25:03.705 --> 00:25:06.585
nothing… lasts forever, right?

00:25:07.585 --> 00:25:09.345
Eventually, everyone must part ways.

00:25:42.865 --> 00:25:44.305
Why are you crying?

00:25:46.465 --> 00:25:49.785
Because I'm so happy to be with you.

00:25:51.185 --> 00:25:52.305
You're being dramatic.

00:25:53.505 --> 00:25:55.185
Don't cry, okay?

00:26:08.585 --> 00:26:09.745
See you soon.

00:26:11.465 --> 00:26:13.025
It’s raining over here.

00:26:13.105 --> 00:26:14.465
Is it raining there too?

00:26:14.545 --> 00:26:17.225
It’s just a bit cloudy.

00:26:17.865 --> 00:26:19.305
Please hurry up.

00:26:20.025 --> 00:26:21.265
Hey,

00:26:21.985 --> 00:26:24.105
don't catch all the fish in the sea.

00:26:24.665 --> 00:26:25.785
Leave some for me.

00:26:26.665 --> 00:26:27.785
See you.

00:26:45.945 --> 00:26:49.265
Nabnueng! It's me!

00:26:57.905 --> 00:26:59.025
Sailom…

00:27:17.145 --> 00:27:18.825
It’s been a long time, Son.

00:27:28.585 --> 00:27:30.625
Don't you dare tell anyone about this.

00:27:32.145 --> 00:27:33.985
Or I'll kill your mother.

00:28:05.105 --> 00:28:08.585
Oh, wow…

00:28:09.385 --> 00:28:11.385
you’ve become much cuter than before.

00:28:13.225 --> 00:28:14.825
Did you miss me?

00:28:18.425 --> 00:28:19.825
I love you, Sailom.

00:28:22.025 --> 00:28:23.225
Come and give Daddy a hug.

00:28:52.185 --> 00:28:53.105
Sailom!

00:28:56.145 --> 00:28:57.345
I’m so sorry

00:28:57.425 --> 00:29:01.225
for not taking care of you
all these years.

00:29:03.185 --> 00:29:04.105
Back then,

00:29:04.185 --> 00:29:06.425
I wasn't ready to be a mother.

00:29:08.345 --> 00:29:10.425
So I gave you to Phailin

00:29:10.505 --> 00:29:12.545
when we were nurses together,

00:29:14.585 --> 00:29:17.945
then I went to start
a new life in Bangkok.

00:29:20.865 --> 00:29:22.825
Can you forgive me?

00:29:36.465 --> 00:29:38.225
I’ve never been angry with you.

00:29:40.225 --> 00:29:41.465
I understand.

00:29:45.625 --> 00:29:47.545
Everyone has their own reasons.

00:30:20.745 --> 00:30:22.065
Thank you…

00:30:23.025 --> 00:30:24.185
so much, Son.

00:30:25.865 --> 00:30:27.385
But there is something…

00:30:28.105 --> 00:30:30.185
I need you to help me with.

00:30:46.825 --> 00:30:49.145
Your grandmother has Meniere's disease.

00:30:49.745 --> 00:30:51.465
It’s not too serious,

00:30:51.545 --> 00:30:54.785
but she needs to avoid stress
and get plenty of rest.

00:30:55.305 --> 00:30:57.505
I'd like her to stay one more night

00:30:57.585 --> 00:31:00.225
for observation, in case of emergency.

00:31:00.305 --> 00:31:02.985
If everything looks good,

00:31:03.065 --> 00:31:05.545
she can go home tomorrow afternoon.

00:31:07.025 --> 00:31:09.065
Thank you, Doctor.

00:31:17.425 --> 00:31:18.385
Are you feeling better?

00:31:21.265 --> 00:31:22.185
Yeah.

00:31:26.105 --> 00:31:27.665
Sorry for calling you last night.

00:31:29.145 --> 00:31:30.665
I didn't know who else to turn to.

00:31:31.785 --> 00:31:33.705
I get it.

00:31:44.505 --> 00:31:45.345
Are you free tomorrow?

00:31:46.145 --> 00:31:46.985
Why?

00:31:48.225 --> 00:31:49.305
Look after my grandma for me.

00:31:49.385 --> 00:31:50.425
What?

00:31:52.425 --> 00:31:54.745
I have work in the morning.

00:31:55.985 --> 00:31:58.665
I'm afraid she'll wake up alone

00:31:58.745 --> 00:31:59.825
and get stressed again.

00:32:02.265 --> 00:32:03.265
Fine.

00:32:04.265 --> 00:32:06.905
Just tell me what your job is tomorrow.

00:32:07.665 --> 00:32:09.305
I'll go do it for you.

00:32:09.825 --> 00:32:11.705
You can take her home yourself.

00:32:11.785 --> 00:32:14.385
You? Doing my job?

00:32:14.985 --> 00:32:16.265
Can you handle it?

00:32:16.905 --> 00:32:17.985
Looking down on me?

00:32:19.785 --> 00:32:21.105
Nope.

00:32:22.785 --> 00:32:23.945
DinDin.

00:32:24.025 --> 00:32:25.145
Grandma.

00:32:26.505 --> 00:32:28.025
How are you? Feeling better?

00:32:29.065 --> 00:32:31.905
Oh, this is Tawan. He’s my boss.

00:32:32.665 --> 00:32:33.665
Hello, Grandma.

00:32:35.065 --> 00:32:37.545
Hello. Thank you so much.

00:32:37.625 --> 00:32:38.985
No problem.

00:33:05.705 --> 00:33:06.785
Sailom!

00:33:07.865 --> 00:33:08.905
Sailom!

00:33:11.185 --> 00:33:12.145
Sailom!

00:33:22.705 --> 00:33:23.785
Sailom!

00:33:30.665 --> 00:33:31.745
Sailom!

00:33:33.265 --> 00:33:34.985
Pi Doc, can you reach Sailom?

00:33:35.065 --> 00:33:38.825
Not at all. I’ve been knocking,
but no one answers.

00:33:38.905 --> 00:33:41.385
Should we break in? Or call the police?

00:33:41.465 --> 00:33:43.105
James! Get a grip!

00:33:44.945 --> 00:33:47.425
-Sailom!
-Sailom!

00:33:48.065 --> 00:33:49.225
Sailom!

00:33:50.585 --> 00:33:53.065
Wait! I remember now.

00:33:53.705 --> 00:33:54.745
The tree pot.

00:34:08.264 --> 00:34:09.185
Found it!

00:34:12.425 --> 00:34:14.784
Come, let’s go inside.

00:34:18.665 --> 00:34:19.824
Sailom!

00:34:23.105 --> 00:34:24.264
Sailom!

00:34:26.065 --> 00:34:27.145
Sailom!

00:34:34.865 --> 00:34:35.784
Sailom!

00:34:42.344 --> 00:34:44.905
-Found him?
-No. What about the backyard?

00:34:44.985 --> 00:34:46.105
Yeah, let’s go.

00:35:03.385 --> 00:35:04.945
Mom! Mom!

00:35:06.265 --> 00:35:07.225
Mom!

00:35:08.945 --> 00:35:10.105
Mom! Mom!

00:35:10.705 --> 00:35:11.865
Mom, help me!

00:35:17.305 --> 00:35:18.225
Sailom!

00:35:20.025 --> 00:35:21.065
Sailom!

00:35:39.145 --> 00:35:40.305
Sailom!

00:36:16.545 --> 00:36:17.705
Sailom.

00:36:19.705 --> 00:36:20.745
Don’t come in.

00:36:21.905 --> 00:36:23.065
Sailom.

00:36:24.305 --> 00:36:26.585
Sailom, it's me.

00:36:27.385 --> 00:36:31.105
-Sailom.
-No! Stay away from me!

00:36:33.785 --> 00:36:35.545
I missed you, Son.

00:36:36.385 --> 00:36:38.065
Come give Daddy a hug.

00:36:45.945 --> 00:36:47.665
No! No!

00:36:47.745 --> 00:36:49.785
-No! Don’t hurt me! No!
-Come on Son!

00:36:49.865 --> 00:36:52.025
Stay away!

00:36:53.625 --> 00:36:56.625
-Come out! I’m your dad!
-No! No!

00:36:56.705 --> 00:36:59.385
I am your dad!

00:36:59.985 --> 00:37:01.705
No one can help you!

00:37:01.785 --> 00:37:04.465
No! No!!

00:37:06.225 --> 00:37:08.465
Get away from me!

00:37:11.865 --> 00:37:13.985
-Sailom, take it easy.
-No!

00:37:14.505 --> 00:37:15.345
Get out!

00:37:16.145 --> 00:37:17.305
Go away!

00:37:20.345 --> 00:37:21.545
Sailom,

00:37:23.185 --> 00:37:25.025
if you can hear me…

00:37:28.665 --> 00:37:30.825
take a deep breath in.

00:37:31.825 --> 00:37:33.825
And slowly breathe out.

00:37:46.745 --> 00:37:48.225
Inhale deeply.

00:37:52.305 --> 00:37:54.425
Exhale slowly.

00:37:56.145 --> 00:37:57.625
Deep inhale.

00:37:58.825 --> 00:38:00.145
Slow exhale.

00:38:02.305 --> 00:38:04.825
Just stay calm, Sailom.

00:38:06.025 --> 00:38:07.385
I'm right here.

00:38:11.065 --> 00:38:12.105
Sailom,

00:38:16.785 --> 00:38:18.705
I’m at your house now.

00:38:20.665 --> 00:38:22.545
You’re in your house.

00:38:24.865 --> 00:38:26.945
And I'm here in your room with you.

00:38:29.985 --> 00:38:31.625
There's nothing to be afraid of.

00:38:35.305 --> 00:38:37.865
When you're ready,

00:38:39.985 --> 00:38:42.345
slowly come out to me.

00:38:44.985 --> 00:38:46.425
You're safe now.

00:39:59.625 --> 00:40:01.425
Come with me, okay?

00:41:48.785 --> 00:41:50.025
Tawan,

00:41:52.785 --> 00:41:54.705
please take me to the toilet.

00:41:54.785 --> 00:41:56.025
Of course.

00:43:05.625 --> 00:43:06.665
Ugh!

00:43:22.345 --> 00:43:24.545
Hey. Hey.

00:43:25.945 --> 00:43:26.905
Boyfriend.

00:43:28.185 --> 00:43:29.425
Oh…

00:43:30.545 --> 00:43:32.785
Look who's here.

00:43:33.305 --> 00:43:34.665
How did you know I was here?

00:43:35.265 --> 00:43:36.985
DinDin told me.

00:43:45.025 --> 00:43:46.465
Come on, let's go home.

00:43:47.585 --> 00:43:48.985
I need to settle the tab.

00:43:49.625 --> 00:43:51.305
No need. I already took care of it.

00:43:52.105 --> 00:43:53.625
You’re so sweet.

00:43:54.425 --> 00:43:56.265
Let's go.

00:43:57.145 --> 00:43:58.305
Can you walk?

00:44:00.665 --> 00:44:01.705
Careful now.

00:44:07.665 --> 00:44:09.025
Nava? What’s wrong?

00:44:10.585 --> 00:44:11.705
Nava. Nava.

00:44:12.825 --> 00:44:13.705
My stomach hurts.

00:44:13.785 --> 00:44:14.665
Ow!

00:44:28.385 --> 00:44:30.145
What’s happening to Nava?

00:44:30.225 --> 00:44:32.465
The patient’s condition
has weakened so much.

00:44:32.545 --> 00:44:35.025
Let’s… try traveling abroad together.

00:44:35.625 --> 00:44:38.585
If that's what you want,
you need to get better first.

00:44:39.265 --> 00:44:41.305
Do you think I can’t afford the bill?!

00:44:41.385 --> 00:44:43.825
Is it a tradition to throw
a punch before we kiss?

00:44:45.945 --> 00:44:51.225
The best form of healing is
rebuilding trust in humanity.

00:44:51.305 --> 00:44:54.545
Is it going to be a burden
to be with a broken man like me?

00:44:54.625 --> 00:44:56.905
In that case… do we try kissing?